result.execSummary:
The defendant NICHOLAS E TILLER was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: of Waiver of Preliminary hearing, Arraignment, Plea & Sentencing held on October 24, 2022, before Hon Mark T. Slate - Circuit Court Judge, by Karen Blair - Court Reporter

4:10 PM Defendant NICHOLAS E TILLER in court, in custody.  Attorney Matthew Steven McElroy in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant states he had a chance to talk with the State. ADA recites offer - exchange for plea to count 1, striking the repeater, State will recommend probation and jail and will dismiss and read in count 2-6. Court concurs - will accept offer. Court instructs defendant of his/her right to counsel. Defendant waives right to counsel. Court accepts waiver. Defendant states he will be waiving the prelim. Court instructs the defendant regarding his/her right to a preliminary examination. Defendant waives his/her right to a preliminary examination. Court finds probable cause. Court accepts the waiver of the prelim and binds the defendant over for trial.  Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY.

State files an information with the court and confirms it mirrors the complain. Defendant acknowledges receipt of the information and waives any reading. Defendant enters a plea of Not Guilty.

Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights. Court goes over the elements of each offense. Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty. Court instructs defendant regarding deportation. (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions. 

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY. Court finds the plea is made knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently. Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea. Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1, striking the repeater and will dismiss and read in the remaining counts 2-6. Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today. Defendant waives right to PSI. ADA concurs - is not requesting a PSI. Sentencing statement by ADA McElroy. Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

-18 months of Initial Confinement and 1 year of Extended Supervision - to commence immediately or to be consecutive to any other sentence if the defendant is currently serving a sentence.
Defendant is eligible for the Earned Release Program and the Challenge Incarceration Program. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:

-Court costs. Court orders the fine and costs in this file shall be paid from all funds received into the defendant's prison accounts in accordance with prison policy. If any fines and/or costs remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision.  If probation/supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.  
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample. 
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent including any counseling and/or treatment and follow-up as recommended. 

Court grants the defendant 53 days of sentence credit.

Court adjourned at 4:34 PM.
Second appearance on October 24, 2022 at 03:00 pm.

8:50 AM Defendant NICHOLAS E TILLER in court, in custody.  Attorney Matthew Steven McElroy in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant qualifies for the public defender's office and is awaiting counsel. Defendant received an offer from the DA. Defendant reads previously prepared statement to the Court. The Court will look at appointing court appointed counsel for the defendant if he is still in custody. Statement by ADA McElroy. Court instructs defendant of his/her right to counsel. Defendant waives right to counsel. Court accepts waiver.  Court sets Status of Counsel for October 24, 2022 at 3:00 PM. 

Court adjourned at: 8:54 AM
Second appearance on October 4, 2022 at 08:45 am.

8:46 AM Defendant NICHOLAS E TILLER in court, in custody.  Attorney Matthew Steven McElroy in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading. Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count and as repeater. Court instructs defendant of his/her right to an attorney.  Court notes bond has been set. Statement by the defendant regarding counsel, if PD's office can't appoint, will request court appointed counsel. Court instructs defendant regarding his/her right to a preliminary hearing. Defendant waives the time limits. Court will set for Status of Counsel on October 4, 2022 at 8:45 AM. Statement by the Court - if an attorney has not been appointed, the Court may entertain appointing one. Defendant requests to waive his right to counsel to talk with the District Attorney. Court instructs defendant of his/her right to counsel. Defendant waives right to counsel. Court accepts waiver. 

Court adjourned at 8:51 AM
Adjourned initial appearance on September 20, 2022 at 08:45 am.

9:08 AM Defendant NICHOLAS E TILLER appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Matthew Steven McElroy in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant has no objection to holding this hearing by zoom. Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading. Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count. Court instructs defendant of his/her right to an attorney.  Defendant states he's contacted the public defender's office. Adjourned initial September 20, 2022 at 8:45 AM 

Court adjourned at 9:10 AM.

1:06 PM Defendant Nicholas Tiller appeared in custody, by video. Atty Scott Nelson appeared by video for Nicholas Tiller.  Attorney Matt McElroy in court for State of Wisconsin. Court has reviewed a probable cause statement and finds probable cause that a crime may have been committed.  ADA makes bond recommendation. Atty Nelson makes bond recommendation. Court orders bond at $5,000.00 cash bond. Court sets initial appearance for September 7, 2022 at 9:00 AM.
